  "title": "Research Fellow (Coastal Engineering)",
  "description": "<p>Interested applicants are invited to apply directly at the <a href=\"https://careers.nus.edu.sg/job/Research-Fellow-%28Coastal-Engineering%29/31567-en_GB/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>NUS\nCareer Portal</strong></a></p><p>Your application will be processed only if you apply\nvia <a href=\"https://careers.nus.edu.sg/job/Research-Fellow-%28Coastal-Engineering%29/31567-en_GB/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>NUS\nCareer Portal</strong></a></p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.<br /></p><h2><strong>Job Description</strong></h2><p>The Department of Civil & Environmental Engineering, National University of Singapore (NUS) invites applications for one (1) Research Fellow position in the area of Coastal Engineering. The candidate is expected to work in investigating multi-phase hydrodynamic interactions, and turbulence modelling with Large Eddy Simulations involving engineering applications in both atmospheric and coastal water environments. <br /> </p><p>The scope can also include:<br /> <br />•    Investigating turbulence dynamics and coherent flow structures induced by extensive marine infrastructure coverage.<br />•    Experimental measurements and corresponding numerical simulations using advanced Computational Fluid Dynamics (CFD) technique of Large Eddy Simulations.<br />•    Assessment of structural stability and environmental impacts associated with coastal protection measures.<br />•    Develop custom software for data integration and visualization of simulation outputs.<br />•    Conduct field experiments in the coastal environment to collect good quality data.</p><h2><strong>Job Requirements</strong></h2><p><br />    Applicants should have a PhD in Civil Engineering or related field. <br />    Preferably with a few years of relevant experience in computational fluid dynamics (CFD) modelling with Large Eddy Simulations involving engineering applications in both atmospheric and coastal water environments.<br />    Strong written and spoken communication skills.<br />    Open to fixed-term contract.</p>",
